SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: The Fund's administrator has analyzed the tax positions taken by the Fund and has concluded that, as of May 31, 2022, there are no uncertain positions taken, or expected to be taken, that would require recognition of a liability or disclosure in the consolidated financial statements. The Fund is subject to routine audits by the taxing jurisdictions; however, there are currently no audits for any tax periods in progress.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 3:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS CONTRACTED WITH THE IRONWORKERS EMPLOYEES' BENEFIT CORPORATION, INC. (IEBC) TO PROVIDE ADMINISTRATIVE SERVICES FOR THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR OF THE IEBC before filing the form 990, AFTER THE APPROVAL OF THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS BY THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: ORGANIZATIONAL DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL INFORMATION ARE AVAILABLE BY APPOINTMENT AT THE ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICE.

THE ADMINISTRATIVE EXPENSES OF THE ORGANIZATION ARE PAID BY THE IEBC, AS TRUST ADMINISTRATOR. THE ORGANIZATION REIMBURSES THE IEBC FOR THESE EXPENSES. IEBC REPORTS PAYMENTS TO VENDORS ON THEIR FORMS 1099.
THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES AND EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR OVERSIGHT OF THE ANNUAL AUDIT AND SELECTION OF THE INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT. THE PROCESS HAS NOT CHANGED FROM THE PRIOR YEAR.
